a volcano on the uninhabited aleutian island of 
kiska erupted for the first time since 1969 spewing steam and ash 
thousands of feet into the sky over the bering sea 
witnesses at a us navy transmitter station on amchitka island 
about 60 miles east of kiska said they saw steam blowing from the 
4000foot volcano friday morning and watched for a few hours before 
weather obscured the view 
