event said victoria avery a scientist at the alaska volcano 
observatory 
the last eruption noted at kiska volcano one of 40 active 
volcanoes in the aleutians lasted six days in september 1969 
officials said 
the uninhabited island occupied by the japanese in world war ii 
and later made a national historic landmark is near the western end 
of the aleutian chain stretching from alaska toward the soviet union 
