in the first debate between perus presidential 
candidates alberto fujimori accused mario vargas llosa of taking 
drugs and vargas llosa attacked his opponent for coming with his 
samurai sword held high 
the twohour televised debate sunday night came a week before the 
runoff election between vargas llosa the internationally known 
novelist and fujimori an agronomist who has capitalized on his 
japanese background and claimed it could help attract foreign 
investment to peru 
fujimori a political unknown when he launched his campaign 
surprised the heavily favored vargas llosa in the firstround 
balloting on april 8 he finished with 246 percent of the vote to 
vargas llosas 276 percent forcing a runoff because no candidate 
received an absolute majority 
