<TEXT>
the social democratic party has dissolved itself 
after nine years of trying to create a moderate third force in 
british politics 
you have to realize sadly that our membership is not large 
enough to lay claim to be a democratic party party leader david 
owen told reporters sunday after the partys national committee 
voted 175 to suspend its constitution 
owen said party membership had collapsed to 6200 from a peak 
68000 soon after the social democrats were launched in january 
1981 party organizers said a number of members had not paid dues 
for the year 
owen is one of three legislators the party has in the 650member 
house of commons the three will continue to hold their seats as 
independent social democrats 
owen and three other former cabinet ministers then leading 
members of the labor party had formed the new party promising to 
break the mold of british politics 
they sought the middle ground between the dominant conservative 
and labor parties hoping to eventually displace labor which they 
accused of going too far to the left 
many analysts predicted labor would never achieve power again 
after prime minister margaret thatcher and her conservatives won a 
second general election victory in 1983 then consolidated it in 
1987 
but the social democrats not only never got within sight of their 
target they never even managed to displace the old centrist liberal 
party with whom they formed an uneasy alliance that won 22 
parliamentary seats in the 1987 general election 
owen refused to merge with the liberals but a majority of his 
party agreed and formed the social and liberal democrats david 
sainsbury a grocery chain multimillionaire told owen he was no 
longer willing to continue his financial backing of the fading party 
meanwhile labor has undergone a rejuvenation under leader neil 
kinnock 
it has dumped leftist policies and extreme leftist members and 
benefited from a slump in popularity for mrs thatchers governing 
conservatives stemming from inflation cuts in the national health 
service and a new tax to finance local services levied on all adults 
instead of just property owners 
