jury selection began today in the drug and 
perjury trial of mayor marion barry as the mayor blasted federal 
prosecutors for using tactics more befitting a totalitarian kind 
of society 
barry 54 has pleaded innocent to all 14 charges against him 
sources close to the case have said his lawyers have been conducting 
plea bargain talks with federal prosecutors 
the mayor accompanied by his wife effi entered the courthouse 
through a side door without speaking to reporters inside the 
courtroom more than 100 potential jurors were given questionnaires 
to fill out designed to gauge their fitness for the jury that will 
hear the case 
in an interview hours earlier with a local radio station the 
thirdterm mayor launched a preemptive strike against the 
prosecution 
its frightening that since 1983 my family have had to go 
through my mail being opened my bank accounts checked my tax 
return looked at my phones tapped 
can you imagine you cant even have a conference in your 
bedroom with your wife for fear that theyre listening to anything 
you may say its been a thing that you thought may happen in a 
totalitarian kind of society 
the mayor also said a local television station has gotten a 
copy of the tape from the prosecutors theyre trying to figure out 
now how to show it he said in an apprent reference to the 
videotape that made during the fbi sting operation that resulted in 
barrys arrest on drug charges on jan 18 
judy smith spokeswoman for us attorney jay b stephens said 
the office would have no comment the station wrctv also said it 
would have no comment 
