foreign ministers from 35 nations open 
an eastwest human rights conference tuesday hoping to rewrite the 
ground rules in europe so they protect ethnic minorities and 
guarantee the rule of law 
backstage us secretary of state james a baker iii and soviet 
foreign minister eduard shevardnadze will press ahead with talks on 
germanys future picking up the thread from the weekend summit in 
washington 
the monthlong conference is likely to produce a final document 
endorsing principles that just one year ago were out of reach free 
elections pluralist politics and freedom of speech assembly and 
religion 
more radical proposals such as establishing a committee to 
mediate ethnic disputes and possibly a security force are likely to 
meet resistance 
