declaration said per fergo who heads the host delegation 
the chief of the us delegation max kampelman said in an 
interview the conference will discuss creating a mechanism to 
mediate disputes involving ethnic minorities he gave as an example 
complaints of discrimination by ethnic hungarians living in romania 
foreign ministers will meet in copenhagen for two days 
delegations led by senior diplomats will draft the final conference 
document 
the copenhagen conference is an outgrowth of the 1975 helsinki 
final act which reduced tensions in europe and set minimum 
standards of behavior by states toward their citizens 
the 35 signatories of the helsinki accords form the conference on 
security and cooperation in europe they are the united states 
canada and all european nations except albania which now wants to 
join 
the first conference was held in paris last june and ended 
without a final document the final meeting will be held in moscow 
in 1991 
first on the agenda for the meeting of foreign ministers is 
creating a committee that will prepare for a summit later this year 
all european nations except bulgaria were sending foreign ministers 
the copenhagen conference takes place in a new europe ripe for 
agreement it also comes as new pillars are being sought to support 
a reshaped europe many leaders look to the conference as the 
foundation of the new structure 
baker and shevardnadze were to continue talks on whether a 
