bars many without being charged or tried 
police set up roadblocks near universities in northwest beijing 
on monday night and would not allow foreign journalists to pass one 
western reporter saw three truckloads of riot police armed with 
shields and rifles entering the university area 
security forces armed with ak47 rifles patrolled outside beijing 
university plainclothes police many with walkietalkies kept an 
eye on students 
for the third night students smashed beer bottles bottle 
in chinese sounds much like senior leader deng xiaopings name but 
there was no repetition of the campus protest sunday night that 
attracted as many as 1000 students 
nothing will happen tonight one student said it would 
just be a repeat of last night and it would not be meaningful 
yesterday was the time for it to happen 
it was on the night of june 3 1989 that the peoples liberation 
army stormed beijing killing hundreds and perhaps thousands of 
people on the way to ending the occupation of tiananmen square by 
students pressing for reform 
beijing university students marched around campus sunday night 
singing the internationale the anthem of the international 
socialist movement which became a theme song during last years 
demonstrations 
the one speaker at the rally 21yearold economics major li 
minqi disappeared monday and was believed to be hiding 
several western journalists were roughed up and briefly detained 
by police during the protest the state department on monday 
denounced the action and said it had advised the chinese government 
that such actions are clearly unacceptable 
a few candles burned in some graduate dormitories monday night 
possibly in memory of those killed several people hooted and spat 
out a dormitory window when a convoy of security drove by 
the 100acre tiananmen square the symbolic center of china is 
usually open to the public but it was surrounded by paramilitary 
police 
a man who tried to hand out leaflets at the gate of the forbidden 
city across from the square was quickly seized by police foreign 
witnesses said western reporters saw police drag off another 
person apparently a woman near the square 
some students called for a hunger strike to mark the anniversary 
but it apparently did not take place some people said theyd get 
drunk one student said 
a hunger strike in may last year began the occupation of 
tiananmen square 
seven protesters outside the chinese embassy in paris held a 
36hour hunger strike that was to end monday night i decided to 
do something concrete for the anniversary so that we wont forget 
what happened and that political prisoners in china may be 
released said yvon thomas 19 who wore a headband with 
freedom and democracy written on it in chinese 
another gathering was held outside the chinese embassy in ulan 
bator the capital of mongolia which has recently undergone 
democratic changes after decades of communist rule 
twenty mongolian students staged a onehour sitin and tried to 
deliver a petition to the embassy but they were not allowed to the 
east german news agency adn said they left after pasting on the 
missions wall a poster condemning the june 4 bloodshed 
the official xinhua news agency reported late monday that beijing 
was stable and life was normal on the anniversary 
millions of beijing residents peacefully spent this monday in 
busy work and pleasant rest it said 
xinhua reported the sunday night protest but stressed that 
beijing campuses were in good order today and quiet as usual 
the government continues to insist that the military crackdown 
was justified saying it faced a counterrevolutionary plot to 
overthrow communist party rule 
the partys official peoples daily said in a frontpage 
editorial monday that the suppression of the democracy movement was 
absolutely correct and necessary 
it said that without resolute action against the demonstrators 
china would be in great chaos now 
