despite reforms that have won mikhail s gorbachev 
praise and admiration in the west human rights abuses still abound 
in the soviet union a monitoring group said monday 
freedom of religion the press and emigration remain restricted 
there are as many as 188 alleged political prisoners and refugees 
from ethnic strife in various soviet republics are forced to live in 
miserable conditions according to the international helsinki 
federation for human rights 
the group meeting in moscow for the first time in its eightyear 
history said it encountered no harassment or intimidation during 
two days of hearings 
