carried signs demanding barrys resignation they were taunted by 
several barry supporters who said the black mayor was the victim of 
racially motivated prosecution and had been entrapped by 
investigators 
if anyone should be on trial it should be us attorney 
stephens said florence smith of the national welfare rights 
organization 
barry attended a church rally sunday night and called the months 
since his jan 18 arrest the most difficult time in my life 
i aint gonna waste time barry said ive come too far 
from where i started from after a standing ovation from the 
crowd he expressed confidence that his legal crisis will not bring 
him down 
while barry has said he needs only one juror to vote against 
convicting him some of his top aides and political advisers have 
indicated they are extremely reluctant to see the case come to trial 
