it was a high school seniors request for a 
bible study class that led to mondays us supreme court ruling 
that allows prayer groups in public schools 
bridget mergens mayhew who has long since graduated from high 
school rejoiced at her legal victory she said it made her feel 
better about the education awaiting her 1yearold daughter 
i never thought that it would go this far mrs mayhew said 
in a telephone interview from offutt air force base where her 
husband is stationed the base is just south of omaha 
in an 81 decision the high court ruled that student prayer 
groups must be allowed to meet at public schools that permit other 
organized extracurricular activities the court said a federal law 
aimed at permitting religious clubs in public schools does not 
violate constitutionally required separation of church and state 
mrs mayhew now 23 was a senior at omahas westside high school 
when school officials turned down her request to start an 
extracurricular club in which members would discuss the bible 
mrs mayhew said there are still students at the 1530student 
high school interested in starting such a club 
i wish we could have had it she said i think it would 
have changed the course of things i think for a lot of people i 
think it would have strengthened a lot of people 
summer vacation began friday at the school principal james 
findley said he knew of one student a senior who graduated this 
year who had been interested in starting a bible study class 
a spokeswoman for the westside community schools district said 
officials were disappointed but would comply with the high court 
ruling 
we just want to analyze it further to see how it affects what 
we have in place said the spokeswoman di saggau 
