<TEXT>
drug policy director william j bennett was on 
course to earn more than 500000 last year before he returned from 
private life to public office according to financial disclosure 
forms released monday 
during the first 2 months before he took office march 10 
bennett earned 80246 from speeches and consulting work plus 
25962 in salary as president of the madison center a private 
policy research group he created 
if the 106208 income from the early months had held up 
throughout 1989 he could have earned about 550000 not including 
interest on savings 
instead the government started paying him after march 10 at the 
rate of 99500 for a full year or about 80000 for the rest of 
1989 
adding that salary to the earnings of the first couple of months 
plus his declared interest earnings gave bennett an approximate 
income of 191209 to 201208 for 1989 
his interest earnings totaled between 5001 and 15000 
bennett known as one of the poorest members of president 
reagans cabinet when he was education secretary saw his income 
zoom after he resigned that job sept 20 1988 thanks to the 
madison center and invitations from across the country to speak 
he realized before he became president bushs director of the 
office of national drug control policy that his earnings would 
nosedive saying at the time well we had a good christmas 
bennett still does not own a home despite his few lucrative 
months he and his wife elayne who works for a project at 
georgetown university funded by the bradley foundation live with 
their two young sons in a rented home in suburban maryland 
his assets went down somewhat last year according to the form 
which does not mention personal property such as automobiles and 
which lists assets only in ranges 
in 1988 bennetts assets ranged from 301003 to 356002 and 
up bennett stated his net worth in early 1989 was about 432600 
not including cars in a financial statement provided to the senate 
judiciary committee that handled his confirmation hearing 
for 1989 bennetts assets ranged from 150002 to 350000 the 
form as filled out by bennett indicated assets of 65002 to 
150000 but spokesman don hamilton responding to a query 
regarding the dramatic drop said the form had been filled out in 
error and would be amended to reflect the higher asset level 
even at the higher level the maximum assets would be about 
82600 less than they were in 1988 
bennett signed a contract in late 1988 with simon amp shuster 
publishers to produce two books and he received advanced royalties 
of 187500 his current financial disclosure form says he will 
receive royalties from the publication of a book yet no book has 
been published 
hamilton said that although bennett completed the manuscript for 
one book it will not be published until he is out of office 
