<TEXT>
president bush on monday declared 19 indiana 
counties a major disaster area from severe storms flooding and 
tornadoes that have struck the state since may 15 
the declaration makes federal funds available to help individuals 
and businesses recover in the counties of brown dearborn franklin 
gibson greene harrison jackson jefferson knox martin ohio 
orange pike posey ripley scott switzerland warrick and 
washington 
the federal government pays up to 75 percent of the cost of 
repairing or replacing public facilities damaged by storms in 
disaster areas 
other aid includes temporary housing grants and lowcost loans 
to cover uninsured property losses 
ronald buddecke of the federal emergency management agencys 
regional office in chicago was named to coordinate the federal 
recovery efforts in indiana 
