federal authorities said monday 
thomas tommy karate pitera a 35yearold martial arts expert 
in the bonanno crime family headed a gang of killers and drug 
dealers who dismembered their victims stuffed them into suitcases 
and plastic bags and buried them in a staten island bird sanctuary 
the authorities said 
federal authorities accused the defendants of at least seven 
murders in the last three years and said they might be responsible 
for about two dozen more 
a raid of piteras brooklyn apartment yielded a library of 
underground publications with such titles as the hitmans 
handbook and kill or be killed 
law enforcement authorities say pitera carried out the 1988 
