<TEXT>
we are witnessing an evolution in international relations of 
increasingly open and massscale human communication 
for a new type of progress throughout the world to become a 
reality everyone must change 
im convinced that we are on the threshold of revising the 
concept of alliance building until now alliances have built on a 
selective and in fact discriminatory basis 
they were based on setting countries against each other they 
divided countries and peoples much more than they united them this 
system that was perfected during the years of the cold war of 
the north atlantic alliance and the warsaw pact but we are 
approaching a time when the very principle of alliance building 
should become different 
i think that both the united states and the soviet union have to 
understand the need for this 
i see many young people here there are many more young people 
outside this room of course and im glad i was able to greet them 
too 
when i conclude my remarks i would like to address them i would 
like to address young people your generation will not only begin 
creating a new world but will also live in it much of it will 
certainly be different from whatever we can imagine now from what 
ive been saying to you here from this rostrum the challenge is to 
make sure that people in that new world live a better life in 
greater freedom much will depend on you the men and women of 
science i wish you success in this great and unprecedented 
undertaking thank you 
