<TEXT>
the us justice department is investigating 
the pricing practices at a network of 19 florida newspapers that 
have grouped together to sell space to large advertisers 
florida newspaper advertising network inc with offices in 
orlando learned of the investigation may 29 when demands for 
records were sent to member newspapers 
alfred e corey jr president of the network said he is puzzled 
by the request because the group is just now being organized 
we have never sold an ad said corey who is advertising 
director of the st petersburg times 
the justice department declined to discuss the case 
the network was formed to make it more convenient for big 
advertisers to reach several markets in the state 
the newspapers which pay membership dues based on their 
circulation have hired new yorkbased sawyer ferguson walker co 
as a third party to organize the network 
corey said the florida group has planned to offer the same prices 
as on the newspapers standard rate cards 
the justice departments civil investigative demand seeks to 
receive by june 25 documents and information related to possible 
pricefixing and market allocation in the sale of print advertising 
in florida 
the demand seeks all documents related to production 
advertising rates sales discounts distribution pricing 
promotion or marketing of advertising inserts 
the demand also seeks all documents related to any proposed or 
actual agreement among florida newspapers related to advertising 
inserts 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
an attorney was awarded 75000 in 
damages by a jury who found he had been defamed when his photograph 
was published as part of a report in the springfield unionnews on 
the sentencing of reputed organized crime figures 
a jury in hampden county superior court on may 29 found that 
anthony j scibelli had been defamed by the republican co 
publisher of the newspaper 
scibelli had claimed that his presence at the federal courthouse 
was not properly explained in the photograph which pictured him 
with one of the defendants or in the accompanying story published 
dec 11 1987 
scibelli claimed mental anxiety and emotional distress in his 
defamation action 
the jury determined the newspaper was negligent and also found 
for scibelli in his claim that he had been discredited and suffered 
mental anguish as a result 
newspaper attorney joseph p pessolano said it is likely motions 
will be filed asking the judge to set aside the jurys findings 
reduce the damage award or grant a new trial 
scibelli did not claim that he had been improperly identified or 
that he had suffered any loss of income as a result of the 
publication he also did not claim that publication of the 
photograph was malicious 
scibelli told the jury that he went to the proceedings to provide 
aid and comfort to his father anthony c scibelli 75 who was 
among the defendants in the racketeering and gambling cases 
he testified he believed the publication of his photograph 
without explanation leaves me there as a defendant 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
prosecutors asked for dismissal of drug 
possession explosives and sexual assault charges against hunter 
thompson saying their case against the gonzo journalist was not 
strong enough 
the dismissal motions may 31 said potential witnesses had not 
cooperated with investigators from the district attorneys office 
a statement from the prosecutors office also said a preliminary 
hearing may 22 resulted in discrepancies between sworn testimony and 
previous statements to investigators 
thompson said the decision was a huge victory for all of us 
and called for a celebratory orgy at his favorite hangout the 
woody creek tavern in aspen 
thompson 53 earlier was ordered to stand trial june 25 on four 
felony and three misdemeanor charges 
the charges stemmed from a visit to his home in woody creek last 
february by gale palmerslater of port huron mich an entrepreneur 
and expornographic film actress and producer she claimed that 
thompson grabbed her breast and threw a drink at her and that she 
saw him sniff cocaine during her hourslong visit to his home 
authorities subsequently searched thompsons home and said they 
found lsd cocaine tranquilizers marijuana and explosives 
thompson claimed the drugs had been left by guests over the years 
and were only turned up because his home was searched with a 
thoroughness inappropriate for a misdemeanor assault charge 
thompson is an author and journalist known for his accounts of 
political campaigns shark hunts in hawaii and the hells angels he 
often has laced his exaggerated firstperson reports with accounts 
of his own drug and alcohol abuse 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
affiliated publications inc parent of the boston 
globe agreed to acquire 80 percent of the common stock of asm 
communications inc which publishes periodicals on the advertising 
and marketing industry 
terms of the agreement were not disclosed 
asm publishes adweek which is a national network of seven weekly 
magazines covering the marketing and communications businesses with 
