newspapers from alabama to oregon 
people see economics as a very complex mystical thing 
said smith a professor of economics at eastern illinois univesity 
but its not that complex much of economics is just basic common 
sense 
for smith it is a crusade most americans do not understand the 
fundamental rules of economics and their ignorance is bad for the 
nation he said 
smith wants to affect national economic debate by teaching the 
public and hes fascinated by the potential 
i think more people are interested in economics and how it 
affects their future than some give them credit for said smith 
im amazed at how many people you can have access to through 
newspapers 
smith said presidents and congress have ignored the fundamental 
rules of economics at the nations expense 
he blames elected officials republicans and democrats liberals 
and conservatives for passing faulty economic programs for 
political gain and failing to tell the public the hard truth about 
taxes and spending 
