dallas morning news 
state district judge david west in houston denied the request may 
30 and entered a judgment against the times herald formalizing the 
may 8 verdict of houston jurors against the newspaper 
during jury deliberations and in the motion for mistrial 
attorneys for the times herald argued that west incorrectly defined 
antitrust law in a manner that was tantamount to an instructed 
verdict against the times herald 
layne kruse one of the times heralds trial attorneys said the 
formal judgment was a necessary step for any appeal 
the times herald had accused the morning news and its parent 
company belo corp of violating state antitrust laws through a 
transaction with universal press syndicate to acquire publication 
rights to 26 features and comics that were appearing in the times 
herald 
the times herald alleged that the contract was an attempt by belo 
corp to acquire a monopoly in the dallas market 
a houston jury voted 102 against the times heralds claim 
</TEXT>
