<TEXT>
professor bernard notin wrote last year that 
the nazi gas chambers never existed french jews who lost relatives 
in the holocaust decided in march to teach him a lesson 
minutes after notin began an evening economics lecture about 60 
jewish leaders students and survivors of the death camps walked 
into his classroom at jean moulin university and took over 
they sat notin in the second row and informed him he could not 
leave then told the 20 students their professor had defiled the 
memory of 6 million jews who perished in hitlers extermination 
program 
look mr notin an aging woman said revealing the number 
nazi guards had tattooed on her forearm how do you explain this 
tattoo we are part of the 80000 french at auschwitz and only 3 
percent came back 
notin a leading member of jeanmarie le pens farright national 
front looked at his shoes some of his students wept horrified by 
the survivors accounts 
the confrontation was a high point in the notin affair which 
has provoked debate on political interference in schools and whether 
laws against bigotry restrict freedom of speech 
a recent wave of antisemitic vandalism contributed an extra 
bitterness it included desecration of graves and mutilation of a 
corpse in a jewish cemetery at carpentras southern france 
all this was bound to happen said jean levy a jewish leader 
in lyon the proposals of le pen are so racist his language is 
the point of no return 
after the classroom takeover notin was suspended as an associate 
law professor at the lyon university and asked to resign from its 
science council 
he continued to teach economics however michel noir mayor of 
lyon threatened on april 19 to block the universitys expansion 
into a publicly owned building unless it acted against notin 
that prompted one of notins few public statements he insisted 
on the right of everyone to his liberty of opinion to defy the 
powers that be to criticize and to doubt 
no one accused him of preaching his ideas in class but 
university officials feel he should not have lent the institutions 
name to those ideas 
on may 14 the 48member administration council of jean moulin 
university voted to begin proceedings to dismiss notin it also 
suspended granting a doctorate to georges pinault a lecturer in 
celtic languages who once described adolf hitler as the greatest 
man of the 20th century 
they cant write in the name of history and academic freedom 
that the gas chambers didnt exist noir said in an interview 
these arent opinions they are crimes 
unlike the us constitution which guarantees free speech 
frances charter allows the government to curb expression 
a 1972 law sets fines for racist or antisemitic statements the 
national assembly recently extended it to cover revisionism 
denying the holocaust occurred 
violators would be barred from public jobs or elected office for 
five years le pen who has called the gas chambers a detail of 
history considers the law undemocratic 
who is charged to say what one can and cannot say in a free 
country he asked in an interview as for jews he said if they 
are french theres no problem im not antisemitic 
le pen insists his partys main political targets are immigrants 
daniel drai 25 a softspoken medical student who led the 
invasion of notins classroom said theres only a small 
difference between revisionism and carpentras revisionism erases 
the dead desecration kills them all over again 
for him mayor noir and others a critique of the media that 
appeared under notins name in the august 1989 edition of the 
academic review economy and society fits the description of 
revisionism 
one paragraph says visiting concentration camps is a hardly 
credible way to prove gas chambers existed and describes accounts 
of survivors as hearsay 
indignation over the article eventually led to allegations that 
many members of le pens national front were among the 400 faculty 
of jean moulin university 
at least 10 known members of the party teach there including 
notin and bernard gollnisch a member of the european parliament 
the university which overlooks the rhone river is named for a 
resistance leader tortured to death in lyon in 1943 by the gestapo 
it was born of tensions at the old university of lyon ii during 
the 1968 student upheavals in france 
lyon ii split in 1973 a new leftwing school with the original 
name offered social sciences and rightist jean moulin took 
business finance and law plus history philosophy and languages 
critics say the university was a natural choice when the national 
front sought to broaden its intellectual base colette demaiziere 
dean of french geography history and letters said the criticism 
was overblown and accused noir the mayor of political opportunism 
how can we reproach someone for belonging to a legal party 
she asked weve never been able to prove someone here 
proselytized for the front and if they did im not sure the 
students would respond 
for students sipping soft drinks in the university cloister the 
notin affair took a back seat to impending final exams 
we dont even think about politics said philippe cumunel a 
23yearold finance major theyve put burdens on our backs we 
dont even care about 
cumunel said he saw nothing wrong with firing notin and added to 
nods from others they should get the communists out of here too 
these stalinists who deny the gulag are no better than the nazi 
regime 
</TEXT>
