justin wilson the celebrated cajun raconteur and 
cook had just spent the day moving into his new house north of new 
orleans across lake pontchartrain 
the man for all seasonings had poured himself a dollop of merlot 
a wine he favors to talk to a telephone caller howm i doin 
im feelin so good it mus be illegal he said lapsing into the 
famed cajun accent thicker than file gumbo 
wilson has been helping make an obscure regional cuisine a 
fundamental part of american cooking since his first cookbook in 
1964 
his first pbs series cookin cajun aired nationwide on pbs 
and cable for more than 10 years 
at 76 wilson is launching his fourth tv cooking show 
louisiana cookin home grown showcasing the fish game 
vegetables spicy culinary style and anecdotes of acadiana his 
beloved south louisiana homeland 
wilson whos appeared on commercial tv for cajun flavor 
potato chips is proud of the new show his first in five years it 
is running or will run on more than 200 public television stations 
across the country 
cajun cooking is the ability to take what you have and create a 
good dish and season it right with salt pepper and a few good 
things like mint or garlic bay leaf cayenne pepper bell pepper 
onion celery wilson said 
it isnt all that hard but so few people know how to take what 
they have and put it together and season it properly he said 
its creative cooking thats all it is 
home grown is not a show to watch hungry 
the opener features brown rice pudding with meringue other 
guest stars are shrimp oysters catfish crawfish rabbit 
venison mirliton andouille and boudin sausage crab okra pecans 
gator greens sweet potato and duck 
i am a gourmet but i am more of a gourmand he explained 
a gourmet is somebody thats an epicurean but a gourmand is 
somebody thats a pig hog and thats what i am 
joostahn is more than that 
wilson who has recorded 27 albums of cajun humor also is the 
