old zombies never die they just stagger 
back for remakes 
the flesheaters that grossed out moviegoers in 1969s night 
of the living dead and its two sequels are back as the lowbudget 
black and white horror classic is remade at an abandoned dairy farm 
about 45 miles southwest of pittsburgh 
the remakes plot like the originals is as simple and 
slowmoving as the shuffling dead themselves 
boy meets girl in cemetery boy and girl meet zombie zombie gets 
hungry eats boy girl flees girl crashes mercedes meets other 
survivors in desolate farmhouse many more zombies get hungry 
people in farmhouse nail boards over doors and windows people 
