editors note hes seen the money roll in and the money roll 
out hes shed a boozing habit a fear of flying and a shaggy 
toupee pete fountain is still playing the kind of dixieland jazz 
his customers want to hear but all in all hed rather be rich 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
pete fountain still has to blow his clarinet 
for a living and he blames it all on zaps from god 
there pete stands coming up on age 60 short square with white 
goatee and mustache bald as a peeled onion hes fronting a 
sevenman band onstage in a lush saloon and regaling a convention 
crowd with smooth dixieland jazz 
fountain calls it a saloon which is his right since he owns the 
joint nightclub might be a more accurate term 
its a jewel of a bandbox crimson and black with gold trim 500 
seats located in a thriving hotel beside the mississippi river at 
the center of new orleans 
sounds like hes all set right 
but heck you always got a pea under the mattress fountains pea 
is that he has played the stuff the crowd likes thousands of times 
bourbon street up a lazy river pleyels hymn new 
orleans memphis blues basin street blues columbus 
stockade blues the yellow dog bluesand on and on 
all grand old tunes but enough already 
what fountain had rather do is be a millionaire lounging beside 
an olympicsize swimming pool behind a plantation house a cool 
glass of sparkling water in hand no more bourbon please hide that 
vodka no worries if he plays he plays what he likes not what 
the crowd likes 
pete might be relaxing by that pool right now except for a slight 
flaw in character he can lose money faster than he can make it 
during 30 years as a saloon owner slaving over a hot clarinet 
onstage or in a recording studio the money rolled in and the 
money rolled out 
ive made it he says but i have also made some very bad 
investments 
the worst one was the purchase of a handsome hotel overlooking 
the blue gulf of mexico in biloxi miss some 70 miles east of new 
orleans 
i thought owning a hotel would be the greatest thing in the 
world he says then i lost it down the tube 
a chunk of fountain money went into the 1984 new orleans worlds 
fair the fair wound up losing all investor input and about 100 
million besides 
other ventures along the way included a string of convenience 
stores zap there was something called petes wieners and famous 
frozen custard zap 
i could write a book on a lot of the things that i got into 
he said 
i used to say if i had the hotel i could play just one day a 
week but naaah its like you know youre gonna play any time i 
try anything else god zaps me its like he said ive given you 
this talent and damn it youre gonna do it youre gonna play no 
matter what 
fountain was playing with trumepter al hirt in a french quarter 
nightclub 32 years ago when his big break came 
it was a call from of all people lawrence welk a shrewd 
entertainer whose square upright musical style was a joke in the 
jazz circles where pete fountain labored 
would mr fountain bring his clarinet and join the welk band as a 
featured sideman yes indeedy 
maybe it wasnt jazz but the welk musical hour was a top 
television show of that day the audience was in the millions 
you didnt get rich with lawrence welk but you got a lot of 
exposure fountain says and he loves jazz 
he spent two years on the show working jazz clubs on the side 
welk always said he would make my name a household word he 
taught me a little i used to want to play the things i wanted to 
play but i realized you have to play the things that people want to 
hear you play not what you want to hear you play 
fountain has hewed to this philosophy through an output of 85 
record albums three of them achieving gold status and 54 guest 
stints on johnny carsons tv show 
fountain and his band made their fifth command performance for 
the president at a state dinner in washington on april 26 
a popular guy around new orleans fountain has one big annual 
blowout that has become a fixture of mardi gras 
the half fast walking club is a sight to behold as fountain and 
about 150 old buddies put on masks and fancy dress and stagger four 
miles through the tremendous crowd packed along the rex parade route 
in addition to working at his own saloon four nights a week 
fountain and his band do onenight stands at conventions or concerts 
here and there 
to do this he overcame a desperate fear of flying 
friends said the only way you got pete fountain on an airliner in 
the old days was to fill him full of booze carry him on board and 
dump him in his seat like a sack of potatoes 
no more 
you have to travel fast if you want to work fat extra gigs in 
faraway places 
those lucrative extras are even more necessary if your hobby is 
acquiring and caring for classic cars 
if you want to play with the cars the rolls royces and 
different things you have to fly to pay for it fountains says 
im a car junkie a car nut 
in giving up on getting rich fountain also gave up hard likker 
maybe a little wine now and then 
long before he gave up booze fountain gave up hair he snatched 
off his toupee and threw it at the drummer during a stand in las 
vegas 20 years ago 
what happened i wanted to keep up with the kids i got two or 
three toupees made a year each time the hair was a little longer 
it got down over my shoulder i finally realized what the hell am i 
trying to do you cant keep up with these kids so that night in 
vegas i got rid of it it was soaking wet with sweat it was like 
wearing a mop on your head 
</TEXT>
