<TEXT>
dawnn lewis star of nbcs a different 
world got her start on the show writing the lyrics for the theme 
song 
the composer stu gardner didnt know me as an actress says 
lewis who broke into show business singing jingles for commercials 
when i auditioned for the role i didnt tell them i cowrote the 
theme until i was hired 
she also has been asked to sing the national anthem at the world 
series provided the san diego padres win the national league 
pennant first 
that invitation came from tom werner the teams new owner and 
partner in carseywerner the production team that created a 
different world 
lewis plays jaleesa vinson an older divorced student at 
fictional hillman college who got her degree at the end of the 
season 
she says she doesnt know what her graduation means for jaleesas 
future 
whether that means i come back as a graduate student or a 
teacher or get a job hasnt been decided she says were 
getting some new writers and well meet with them in the summer to 
talk about our characters 
lewis is the only member of the cast from the pilot whos still 
with the show it made its debut three years ago as a spinoff of 
the cosby show starring lisa bonet 
bonet married to musician lenny kravitz left at the end of the 
first season when she became pregnant and has since returned to the 
bill cosby show 
the show also stars jasmine guy as a spoiled debutante plus 
kadeem hardison cree summer charnele brown darryl bell glynn 
turman sinbad and lou myers 
jaleesa is honest young at heart sassy and always has 
something to say about someone elses opinion lewis says she 
makes comments that you cant get mad about because theyre true 
jaleesas in focus she has a game plan she wants to be 
stylish although she doesnt always hit the mark 
lewis grew up in brooklyn and during high school rode the subway 
for an hour and 20 minutes every day to attend new yorks high 
school of music and art in harlem 
id get to school an hour early she says id meet my 
friends for breakfast and no matter how early i got there i was 
always late for my first class 
she was accepted by several colleges but chose the university of 
miami and graduated magna cum laude in 1982 with a degree in music 
i applied to brooklyn college to please my parents she says 
i graduated from high school when i was 16 and i wanted to leave 
new york the temptation to get a job was too strong if i stayed 
there so i wanted to get away my grandmother had recently moved to 
miami so that made it easier on my parents 
i was miamis first musical graduate she says 
i was the kind of kid who would figure out something and make 
it work you couldnt tell me i couldnt do it 
although lewis lives in los angeles where she is active in 
community volunteer work she still considers new york her home she 
has bought a house here and is working on music for a new album 
i thought when i came here that being on television would be my 
biggest adjustment she says just being here is the biggest 
adjustment im not an la person its so different the energys 
different 
the standards are different a 16yearold here can have a car 
at 16 i was worried about having enough tokens for the bus and 
subway 
and coming here as a celebrity makes it even harder because you 
have to fit into a mold you have to drive the right kind of car 
you have to see the right people you have to say the right thing 
</TEXT>
