march 19 monday 
my father is dying 
it is my worst childhood dread the terror in the night come 
true i sit by his bed and hold his hand trying to ward off my 
fears i am failing in my duty i cannot save him 
there is a scene in the film terms of endearment where the 
mother stands at the nurses station and screams for another pain 
shot for her terminally ill daughter now i too stand at a nurses 
station and say quietly politely i think it is time for my dads 
shot 
they look up at me these kids many of them young enough to be 
