<TEXT>
back to school can often mean back to minor health problems for 
children but its nothing parents should worry about says the 
chief of pediatrics at a new york hospital 
many school children go through a period of getting sick again 
after a relatively healthy summer says dr joseph abularrage of 
new york infirmarybeekman downtown hospital this is because 
school and day care programs put children in big groups in confined 
areas unlike their comparatively open surroundings in the summer 
the result is often a mild cold or other easily transmitted minor 
health problem he says 
abularrage says a healthy diet and plenty of rest are the best 
ways to prevent minor illnesses like the common cold but parents 
should be sure to have their children vaccinated 
parents may also have to deal with school phobia if a 
youngster is extremely fearful of going to school and does 
everything to resist going abularrage says the best way to 
handle the situation is to work out the problems of separation 
anxiety very slowly with the child perhaps using the help of a 
counselor or the family doctor 
according to richard oberfield a clinical associate professor of 
child psychiatry at new york university medical center there are 
some common signs of first day jitters 
unusual clinging behavior 
toilet problems 
stomach aches 
insomnia 
new fears 
any behavior that seems regressive for your child such as 
whining or crying 
he suggests that parents go over in detail ahead of time exactly 
what will happen in school and assure the child that you or a family 
member will be there at the end of the school day 
oberfield says parents should consider their own fears as well 
children pick up on unspoken tensions and frustrations he says and 
it is not uncommon for parents to have mixed feelings about sending 
their child off to school 
coming to grips with your own fears should give your child the 
necessary positive reinforcement he says 
