to a physician for a checkup he says 
another sign of visual problems he says is when children 
complain they cant read the print on the tv set a possible 
indication of nearsightedness 
if children have astigmatism the signs will be different 
says roberts they will typically mistake 3s for 8s and 8s for 3s 
sometimes they will also confuse 4s and 5s 
television viewing habits may also indicate hearing problems 
children may increase the tv volume show inattentiveness while 
watching their favorite shows and say what more often when 
comments are made to them according to dr w shain schley these 
signs do not automatically mean a child has a hearing loss but they 
do indicate the need for a physical examination he says 
schley is associate professor of clinical otorhinolaryngology and 
director of the eye nose and throat service at new york 
hospitalcornell medical center 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

