the hong kong company without completing a full check of the 
enduser 
the official also conceded that his ministry should have examined 
the deal more closely 
but at that point the export control was not as strictly 
enforced as it is today and we cant really blame toshiba machine 
or export control staff of the ministry said the official 
speaking on condition of anonymity 
exporting certain hightech equipment to communist countries 
violates japanese export control law and the cocom an international 
agreement of the coordinating committee for multilateral export 
control aimed at keeping certain sophisticated technology out of 
communist hands 
the regulations also require strict identification of the 
enduser of such equipment in countries to which export is 
permitted but in the sale to hong kong the middlemen and buyer of 
record have all apparently disappeared 
toshiba machine officials say they sold the equipment to a hong 
kong company called scientific instruments ltd but such a company 
does not exist at the address stated in the contract the ap 
telephoned a company by the same name located at a different 
address in hong kong but officials there said their company 
specializes in handling medical equipment and never had such a 
machine 
a hong kong trading company that financed and mediated the 
transaction tradecity investment also was not located at the 
address stated in the contract 
toshiba machine officials said their staff in hong kong made 
inquiries but could not find the factory where scientific 
instruments said the sensitive equipment was to be installed 
the officials explained that scientific instruments had not 
prepared a suitable factory and did not permit toshiba engineers to 
install the equipment so toshiba machine refused to guarantee 
performance of the machinery worth 451 million yen then equivalent 
to 2 million 
last time we saw the machine was when unopened wooden boxes 
were placed in a factory in hong kong in may 1985 said takanori 
yamada director of the corporate planning department of toshiba 
machine we never saw the machine after then there was no 
further contact with scientific instruments he said 
toshiba machine officials said they believed the machine wouldnt 
be resold elsewhere because hong kong authorities gave the import 
permission on condition that it be used only in hong kong 
we are quite confident that we did every possible check back 
then matsumoto said if you tell us today that our machine is 
not in hong kong all i can say is it is way beyond our control 
he stressed that the company had tightened its export control 
system in 1987 and the hong kong deal could not have happened 
under the present system but the atmosphere back then was somewhat 
looser than today 
japanese law also was tightened after the 1987 scandal and while 
some cocom violations have been reported the severe penalties on 
toshiba machine and toshiba are widely thought to have had a 
deterring effect 
