<TEXT>
citicorp said it will stop underwriting 
distribution and trading of municipal securities cutting 35 jobs in 
another sign of wall streets slowdown 
glen sergeon managing director of citicorp securities markets 
inc said monday the municipal finance division would cut about 
half of its 70 jobs but is trying to find jobs for displaced workers 
in other areas of the big bank holding company 
we are having an honest react to current market conditions 
he said the marketplace has a lot of excess capacity in it that 
isnt going away quickly 
sergeon said citicorp would concentrate on creating and offering 
derivative products in municipal finance rather than underwriting 
such products typically allow issuers to hedge interest rate and 
other risks 
citicorp is the latest of major underwriters to scale back its 
business in the municipal bond field because of a slowdown in 
issuing taxexempt securities stemming mainly from the tax reform 
act of 1986 
sergeon said the market peaked in 1986 when 320 billion in 
municipal bonds were issued and underwriters received 11 a bond in 
1989 the total number of issues was 118 billion and underwriters 
made 7 a bond 
the amount of human and capital capacity dedicated to this 
marketplace has not adjusted commensurate to the size of the 
market he said 
citicorp said the cuts will not affect other services to 
municipal bond issuers such as investment agreements shorterterm 
distribution agreements and various credit services 
